<subSubSection id="A5D06562FFF2E65EF4BE20F8A5F3F800" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="ED7536E9FFF2E65EF4BE20F8A5F3F800" blockId="0.[151,1437,1546,2035]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis id="DFBEEAFBFFF2E65EF4BE20F8A66BF95D" bold="true" box="[151,359,1758,1782]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" reason="1">Revised diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small to medium-sized mesochrysopids (forewing length of 
<taxonomicName id="2ACA4D6AFFF2E65EF7DC20F8A23CF95D" authorityName="Cao, Wang &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2021" box="[1013,1328,1758,1782]" class="Insecta" family="Mesochrysopidae" genus="Burmotachinymphes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilobata">
<emphasis id="DFBEEAFBFFF2E65EF7DC20F8A23CF95D" box="[1013,1328,1758,1782]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">Burmotachinymphes bilobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<quantity id="2A329B0CFFF2E65EF11E20F9A294F95D" box="[1335,1432,1759,1783]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" unit="mm" value="12.7">12.7 mm</quantity>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2ACA4D6AFFF2E65EF4BE2124A6BFF8B1" authority="Chen &amp; Chen &amp; Deng &amp; Yang &amp; Shi &amp; Ren, 2022" authorityName="Chen &amp; Chen &amp; Deng &amp; Yang &amp; Shi &amp; Ren" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,435,1794,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Mesochrysopidae" genus="Burmotachinymphes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pengi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="DFBEEAFBFFF2E65EF4BE2124A6BFF8B1" box="[151,435,1794,1818]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">Burmotachinymphes pengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="DFBEEAFBFFF2E65EF5932125A503F8B0" bold="true" box="[442,527,1795,1819]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C48D5780FFF2E65EF5932125A503F8B0" box="[442,527,1795,1819]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is more than 
<quantity id="2A329B0CFFF2E65EF6B42125A5EBF8B1" box="[669,743,1795,1819]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
by estimation). In forewing and hind wing, crossveins in RP area (i.e., RP+MA area in 
<bibRefCitation id="895B4B18FFF2E65EF5502101A52EF894" author="Cao, L. R. &amp; Wang, B. &amp; Liu, X. Y." box="[377,546,1830,1855]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="1" refId="ref2211" refString="Cao, L. R., Wang, B. &amp; Liu, X. Y. (2021) A new genus and species of Mesochrysopidae (Neuroptera) from the mid-Cretaceous Burmese amber. Palaeoentomology, 4 (1), 077 - 084. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / PALAEOENTOMOLOGY. 4.1.12" type="journal article" year="2021">
Cao 
<emphasis id="DFBEEAFBFFF2E65EF5832101A6D4F895" box="[426,472,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">et al</emphasis>
., 2021
</bibRefCitation>
) forming multiple gradate series; MA (i.e., MP 
<quantity id="2A329B0CFFF2E65EF0312101A337F895" box="[1048,1083,1830,1855]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="895B4B18FFF2E65EF0682101A3E6F894" author="Cao, L. R. &amp; Wang, B. &amp; Liu, X. Y." box="[1089,1258,1830,1855]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="1" refId="ref2211" refString="Cao, L. R., Wang, B. &amp; Liu, X. Y. (2021) A new genus and species of Mesochrysopidae (Neuroptera) from the mid-Cretaceous Burmese amber. Palaeoentomology, 4 (1), 077 - 084. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / PALAEOENTOMOLOGY. 4.1.12" type="journal article" year="2021">
Cao 
<emphasis id="DFBEEAFBFFF2E65EF05B2101A3ACF895" box="[1138,1184,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">et al</emphasis>
., 2021
</bibRefCitation>
) simple. MP and CuA (i.e., MP2 and CuA in 
<bibRefCitation id="895B4B18FFF2E65EF5E8216DA561F8C8" author="Cao, L. R. &amp; Wang, B. &amp; Liu, X. Y." box="[449,621,1866,1891]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="1" refId="ref2211" refString="Cao, L. R., Wang, B. &amp; Liu, X. Y. (2021) A new genus and species of Mesochrysopidae (Neuroptera) from the mid-Cretaceous Burmese amber. Palaeoentomology, 4 (1), 077 - 084. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / PALAEOENTOMOLOGY. 4.1.12" type="journal article" year="2021">
Cao 
<emphasis id="DFBEEAFBFFF2E65EF5DA216DA52EF8C9" box="[499,546,1866,1890]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">et al</emphasis>
., 2021
</bibRefCitation>
) with marginal multiple pectinate branches in all wings (i.e., more than four marginal pectinate branches). No coalesced condition between RP, MA, MP and CuA in all wings. Longitudinal veins easily distinguished. Other diagnosis as 
<bibRefCitation id="895B4B18FFF2E65EF66A21B5A5F7F800" author="Cao, L. R. &amp; Wang, B. &amp; Liu, X. Y." box="[579,763,1938,1963]" pageId="0" pageNumber="597" pagination="1" refId="ref2211" refString="Cao, L. R., Wang, B. &amp; Liu, X. Y. (2021) A new genus and species of Mesochrysopidae (Neuroptera) from the mid-Cretaceous Burmese amber. Palaeoentomology, 4 (1), 077 - 084. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / PALAEOENTOMOLOGY. 4.1.12" type="journal article" year="2021">
Cao 
<emphasis id="DFBEEAFBFFF2E65EF65C21B5A5A8F801" box="[629,676,1938,1962]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="597">et al</emphasis>
. (2021)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
